From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: EvilOlaf <werner@armbian.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 18:50:05 +0200
Subject: [ARCHEOLOGY] bt-hci: ignore -22 for uwe5622

> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > The Marlin (uwe5622) Bluetooth controller reports HCI_OP_WRITE_DEF_LINK_POLICY
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > as supported but rejects it with -22 (EINVAL) during initialization, causing
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > the entire HCI setup to fail and the controller to remain unusable.
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > Work around this firmware quirk by ignoring -22 errors specifically for
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > WRITE_DEF_LINK_POLICY (0x080f), allowing initialization to continue.
> X-Git-Archeology: - Revision fbda8dec1e3f0fae359caa3f38eccb4dd2002b0b: https://github.com/armbian/build/commit/fbda8dec1e3f0fae359caa3f38eccb4dd2002b0b
> X-Git-Archeology:   Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 18:50:05 +0200
> X-Git-Archeology:   From: EvilOlaf <werner@armbian.com>
> X-Git-Archeology:   Subject: bt-hci: ignore -22 for uwe5622
> X-Git-Archeology:
---
 net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c b/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c
@@ -270,6 +270,13 @@ int __hci_cmd_sync_status_sk(struct hci_dev *hdev, u16 opcode, u32 plen,
 		if (!event)
 			bt_dev_err(hdev, "Opcode 0x%4.4x failed: %ld", opcode,
 				   PTR_ERR(skb));
+
+		/* Ignore -22 for WRITE_DEF_LINK_POLICY - some controllers
+		 * report it as supported but reject it (e.g., Marlin/uwe5622)
+		 */
+		if (PTR_ERR(skb) == -EINVAL && opcode == 0x080f)
+			return 0;
+
 		return PTR_ERR(skb);
 	}
 
